<p>My application behaves strangely. Sometimes, after the application starts, no touch events are raised. To make them work I need to restart the application.<br> Example of my touch event:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;Button Canvas.Bottom="50" Canvas.Right="50" Content="Send" Style="{StaticResource WindowButtonStyle}"&gt;     &lt;i:Interaction.Triggers&gt;         &lt;i:EventTrigger EventName="TouchDown"&gt;             &lt;ei:CallMethodAction TargetObject="{Binding}" MethodName="OnTouchDownSend"/&gt;         &lt;/i:EventTrigger&gt;     &lt;/i:Interaction.Triggers&gt; &lt;/Button&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Has anyone any ideas what can cause such behavior?</p>